summary.name: Car Specifications
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains information about various car models, their fuel efficiency, engine specifications, and origin.

properties.description: The name of the car model.
The fuel efficiency of the car in miles per gallon.
The number of cylinders in the car's engine.
The engine displacement of the car in cubic inches.
The horsepower of the car's engine.
The weight of the car in pounds.
The acceleration of the car in seconds (0-60 mph).
The year the car model was released.
The country or region where the car was manufactured.

goals.question: What is the distribution of car models by origin?
goals.visualization: bar chart of count of car models by origin
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the proportion of car models manufactured in each country or region.

goals.question: What is the relationship between engine displacement and horsepower?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of engine displacement vs horsepower
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the correlation between engine displacement and horsepower, which can provide insights into the performance of the car.

goals.question: What is the distribution of car weight by number of cylinders?
goals.visualization: box plot of car weight by number of cylinders
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the relationship between the number of cylinders and the weight of the car, which can provide insights into the performance and fuel efficiency of the car.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fuel efficiency by year?
goals.visualization: line chart of average fuel efficiency by year
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the trend in fuel efficiency over time, which can provide insights into the impact of regulations and technological advancements.

goals.question: What is the distribution of car acceleration by origin?
goals.visualization: histogram of car acceleration by origin
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the difference in car acceleration between different countries or regions, which can provide insights into the design and performance of the cars manufactured in each location.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.countplot(x='Origin', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of car models by origin?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Car Models')
    plt.legend(title='Origin', loc='upper right', labels=data['Origin'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Displacement', y='Horsepower', hue='Origin', palette='deep')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between engine displacement and horsepower?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Origin')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year
    avg_mpg_by_year = data.groupby('Year')['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=avg_mpg_by_year, x='Year', y='Miles_per_Gallon', marker='o')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fuel efficiency by year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Miles per Gallon')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Fuel Efficiency', loc='upper left')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Acceleration', hue='Origin', kde=True, bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of car acceleration by origin?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Car Acceleration (0-60 mph)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Origin', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
